
[1]expostulation

   EXPOSTULA'TION, n. Reasoning with a person in opposition to his
   conduct; the act of pressing on a person reasons or arguments against
   the impropriety of his conduct,and in some cases, demanding redress or
   urging reformation.

   1. In rhetoric, an address containing expostulation.
